<TITLE> Delwar condemns no-access to Khaleda's </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 23 (bdnews24.com)The government showed its 'parochial attitudes' in barring visitors from entering opposition chief Khaleda Zia's residence on the Eid day, BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain said in a statement issued on Wednesday. He alleged that by not allowing around 50 visitors including retired government officials, political leaders and workers, top business people, other professionals and personal staff to go to her house on Shaheed Mainul Road in Dhaka cantonment, the government only revealed its lowly design of segregating the opposition BNP chief from the people. "Visiting people at their residences on the Eid day and exchanging greetings is an inseparable part of the Eid culture and tradition. Stopping people from visiting an ex-prime minister on this auspicious day was extremely deplorable," said Delwar in his statement. Khaleda had exchanged Eid greetings with people from broad social spectrum at the Ladies' Club in Eskatan Garden on Monday. "The incident went against all democratic norms and culture also. Once again it showed that the innate undemocratic nature of the Awami League hasn't changed at all. Their vengeful ways spare nobody, even on a day when a religious festival was being observed." On Tuesday, BNP and associate organisations protested the incident. b
